  description: 'The language of the Diné (Navajo) people of the American Southwest  -  the most widely spoken Native American language (~170,000 speakers). Famous for its extreme complexity and its use as an unbroken military code by Navajo Code Talkers in WWII. An Athabaskan language with SOV order, four tones, and extraordinarily complex verb morphology.',
